        "orario": "17:50",
        "timestamp": 1773075021,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Europe showing it is 'prepared but does not want to be dragged into a war it wasn't consulted on' Europe Issued on: 09/03/2026 - 17:50 French President Emmanuel Macron is visiting the Charles de Gaulle aircraft carrier, currently off the coast of Crete and heading towards Cyprus. It had been dispatched days before after the island was targeted by a Shahed drone-attack. FRANCE 24 's Kethevane Gorjestani looks at how Europe is reacting to the ongoing conflict in the Middle East. Jailed Istanbul mayor goes on trial in corruption case slammed as political 09/03/2026 Europe 'This is all about defence': Macron addresses European security in Cyprus 09/03/2026 Europe Replay: Emmanuel Macron addresses Iran threat to EU member Cyprus 09/03/2026 Europe Europe rallies around Cyprus after Iranian strikes 09/03/2026 Europe Donald Trump seeks Kyiv's help in defending against Iranian drones 06/03/2026 Middle East US and Middle East countries seek Ukraine's support in drone protection 05/03/2026 Europe Trump threatens to cut off trade with Spain over Iran war refusal 03/03/2026 Europe France to boost nuclear arsenal, could deploy atomic weapons to European allies 02/03/2026 Europe Europe 'exposed to the consequences' of US-Israel's conflict with Iran 02/03/2026 Europe"
